16:25.319 --> 16:26.737
Alright.

16:27.446 --> 16:28.822
Oh my god.

16:28.822 --> 16:31.533
A lung just became
available for my patient!

16:31.533 --> 16:32.910
Yes! Oh!

16:32.910 --> 16:34.786
Honey, oh...

16:34.786 --> 16:37.497
Oh, it's all over your shirt.
‐ It's okay.

16:38.081 --> 16:41.293
‐ Babe, I am so sorry,
but I have to get back to LA.

16:42.503 --> 16:45.380
‐ Hey, hey. Look, my sister's
hanging out with your friends.

16:45.380 --> 16:47.549
She's kind of a loner, so I
really want her to meet people.

16:49.718 --> 16:51.929
‐ Yeah. Seems like
they're really hitting it off.

16:51.929 --> 16:54.056
‐ Mm.
‐ Hey,

16:54.056 --> 16:56.141
as soon as my phone powers on,
I'm out of here,

16:56.141 --> 16:58.936
but I wanted to tell you,
you can't give up on love

16:58.936 --> 17:01.647
just because of your proposal fail.

17:01.647 --> 17:03.899
I know that there is
a Brooklyn Bridge girl

17:03.899 --> 17:05.984
out there for you somewhere.

17:07.778 --> 17:09.780
‐ Am I supposed to know what that is?
Because you look like

17:09.780 --> 17:11.490
you practically moved yourself
to tears just now,

17:11.490 --> 17:13.659
but I have no idea
what you're talking about.

17:14.409 --> 17:16.954
‐ It's this thing I made up.
‐ Okay.

17:16.954 --> 17:19.706
‐ See, I've lived in New York
since college,

17:19.706 --> 17:22.084
but I've never walked across
the Brooklyn Bridge,

17:22.084 --> 17:23.961
and after a while,
I waited so long

17:23.961 --> 17:27.172
that I decided I would wait
and walk it with my soulmate.

17:29.132 --> 17:31.718
‐ You're one of those people whose parents
actually stayed married, aren't you?

17:31.718 --> 17:33.095
College sweethearts,

17:33.095 --> 17:34.680
married for 30 years sort of thing.

17:34.680 --> 17:36.181
So you're like, if they found each other,

17:36.181 --> 17:37.766
there must be someone
out there for everyone.

17:37.766 --> 17:39.643
Blah, blah, blah, blah, blah. Right?

17:40.185 --> 17:42.229
‐ Yeah. Something like that.

17:42.980 --> 17:44.439
‐ Must be nice.

17:44.439 --> 17:47.401
Those of us who grew up
in the real world, not so sure.

17:48.193 --> 17:49.945
Looks like your phone's back.
‐ Yes!

17:51.154 --> 17:52.990
Aw.

17:52.990 --> 17:56.118
Ian sent me a pic holding his
boarding pass and looking sad.

17:56.118 --> 17:58.662
‐ Aww.
‐ I'm gonna call him.

18:00.372 --> 18:01.874
Wait, look.

18:03.208 --> 18:04.668
I can see all of his flight info.

18:05.210 --> 18:07.838
‐ Cool. He's got TSA PreCheck.

18:07.838 --> 18:10.090
‐ He would!

18:10.090 --> 18:12.426
I've always talked
about getting that.

18:12.426 --> 18:14.094
But it's like a whole thing.
No, not the point.

18:16.180 --> 18:19.141
I'm going to go to JFK
and tell him that we're meant to be.

18:19.141 --> 18:21.935
‐ Really?
‐ Hey, uh, can I borrow your car?

18:21.935 --> 18:23.854
I need to take Hannah to the airport.

18:23.854 --> 18:26.356
‐ What?
‐ Emergency surgery calls.

18:26.356 --> 18:29.276
‐ Seems like the universe wants me
to take everyone to the airport.

18:29.276 --> 18:30.944
‐ Alright. Let's go.
‐ Okay. What, are you coming?

18:30.944 --> 18:32.196
‐ I am! Oh!

18:33.322 --> 18:34.698
‐ Wait!

18:34.698 --> 18:36.909
You can't leave me alone with Charlie.
I think I hate him.

18:37.951 --> 18:39.953
‐ We live with him.
‐ I know!

18:41.538 --> 18:44.958
‐ Valentina, don't abandon me!
I have nowhere to go!

18:44.958 --> 18:47.252
I'll need to sell my body to survive!

18:50.172 --> 18:52.174
‐ Hey, sis!
Uh, we're all going to the airport.

18:52.925 --> 18:54.134
‐ You forgot me, didn't you?

18:54.134 --> 18:56.011
‐ What? Who could for‐‐

18:56.011 --> 18:57.429
Yeah. Completely forgot you. I'm sorry.

19:03.352 --> 19:05.646
FUTURE SOPHIE:
And so, we all went to JFK

19:05.646 --> 19:08.815
to tell him that I wanted us
to be together.

19:10.067 --> 19:11.568
‐ There he is.

19:12.903 --> 19:15.572
‐ Oh god, don't let this be
the next Proposal Fail.

19:15.572 --> 19:17.449
Wait! Aren't you‐‐

19:17.449 --> 19:20.702
‐ It's actually Mr. Proposal Fail,
but yes.

19:22.120 --> 19:22.704
‐ Ian!

19:23.956 --> 19:26.124
‐ Sophie? What are you‐‐

19:26.124 --> 19:28.001
‐ I've been on 87 Tinder dates this year.

19:28.001 --> 19:30.379
Okay, all of them were duds.

19:30.379 --> 19:33.465
Just to be clear, I don't do,
like, sexy stuff with all the guys.

19:33.465 --> 19:36.718
A lot of the times, I just have
a white wine and talk.

19:36.718 --> 19:39.012
I also want to be clear
that I am not judging anyone

19:39.012 --> 19:40.472
who does hook up on every date.

19:40.472 --> 19:42.474
It's just not my style.
But if it's someone else's,

19:42.474 --> 19:44.268
that's her business,
and it's nothing to be ashamed of.

19:44.268 --> 19:46.228
‐ This is getting away from her.

19:47.271 --> 19:49.982
‐ Look, what I'm trying to say is that

19:49.982 --> 19:51.859
we live in confusing times,

19:51.859 --> 19:54.194
where it's really hard to meet someone

19:54.194 --> 19:56.363
and‐and‐and connect and have it feel...

19:57.698 --> 19:58.740
Easy.

19:59.408 --> 20:02.160
And tonight, it felt easy.

20:03.328 --> 20:04.621
Other than the Australia thing,

20:04.621 --> 20:07.332
which feels insurmountably hard,

20:07.332 --> 20:08.667
but we can get through it.

20:10.169 --> 20:11.670
I know that we can.

20:13.130 --> 20:15.174
What do you say?

20:17.551 --> 20:19.970
‐ Sophie, I'd love
to make it work, but...

20:20.804 --> 20:23.348
it's a 14‐hour time difference,

20:23.348 --> 20:25.267
and I'm gonna be living

20:25.267 --> 20:27.895
out at sea for weeks
on end without service.

20:28.645 --> 20:31.148
It'd just be way too hard.

20:31.148 --> 20:33.108
‐ Oh, this is brutal.

20:34.735 --> 20:36.695
‐ I'm really sorry, Sophie.

20:36.695 --> 20:39.072
But, maybe someday, right?

20:39.072 --> 20:41.700
‐ Yeah. Maybe.

20:52.961 --> 20:55.672
But I didn't
want to wait around for some day.

21:02.221 --> 21:03.972
‐ I'm doing it!

21:03.972 --> 21:07.184
I'm walking the bridge
without the love of my life!

21:08.143 --> 21:10.354
Sounded more triumphant in my head.

21:10.354 --> 21:11.647
‐ You walk that bridge, girl.

21:12.898 --> 21:16.109
That... surprisingly clean and...

21:16.109 --> 21:17.611
actually rather majestic bridge.

21:17.611 --> 21:20.322
‐ You don't have to pretend
to like this for me.

21:21.657 --> 21:23.283
‐ I'm not pretending.

21:23.283 --> 21:25.786
You know,
I‐I really do think it's stunning.

21:26.912 --> 21:29.790
Brimming with...
with life and personality.

21:33.293 --> 21:34.795
Like you.

21:36.880 --> 21:40.467
‐ Charlie, do you know one of
the reasons I fell so hard for you?

21:41.009 --> 21:44.096
‐ Because my charm is all boy,
but my body is all man?

21:44.930 --> 21:46.682
‐ No.

21:46.682 --> 21:48.642
It's because I thought you were brave.

21:49.476 --> 21:52.604
You've lived this
incredibly pampered life,

21:52.604 --> 21:54.314
but you walked away from it all.

21:55.190 --> 21:57.359
To take a chance on us.

21:59.069 --> 22:00.863
Charlie...

22:00.863 --> 22:02.906
this city is magic!

22:04.199 --> 22:05.826
And so am I.

22:08.579 --> 22:11.623
Do you wanna be a part
of that magic or not?

22:13.208 --> 22:14.710
‐ I do.

22:15.377 --> 22:17.004
Very, very much.

22:23.177 --> 22:26.555
‐ If Sophie can walk across
this bridge totally alone

22:26.555 --> 22:28.098
